<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-10-04">October 4,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 195]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            telegram of the 28th ultimo, reading as follows:<note n="a" xml:id="d204fna">Supra.</note></p>
                        <p>You will continue pressure for the customs-houses, and you will inform
                            the Chinese Government that the demand as to Newchwang will be renewed
                            with increased emphasis if the present condition is allowed to
                            continue.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>